  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Many controllers initialize with the `chainId` or `networkType` set to `1` or `MAINNET` respectively, because that is the default network. The configuration gets updated whenever the network state changes, but until the first state change it might be invalid.\r\n\r\nAs a general rule we should ensure the initial `chainId`/`networkType` is set via the actual network controller state, passed in via the constructor.",
